name: WPI_Number
description: Each port and place contained in this dataset is given a unique number by the publisher. WPI numbers remain consistent between updates and are also referenced in NGA Sailing Directions.

name: Region_Name
description: Region Names, as given in the 2019 edition of the World Port Index, are included.

name: Main_Port_Name
description: Main Port Name, with no diacritical marks. In general, port names listed are approved by the U.S. Board on Geographic Names.

name: Alternate_Port_Name
description: Alternate, conventional, or familiar names may be included here.

name: UN_LOCODE
description: Given in accordance with the United Nations Code for Trade and Transport Locations.

name: Country_Code
description: Country name according to U.S. Government's Geopolitical Entities, Names, and Codes (GENC) standard.

name: World_Water_Body
description: The relevant body of water, as defined by the United States Department of Defense.

name: Sailing_Direction_or_Publication
description: The publication number and title of the NGA Sailing Directions, describing the port or area in which the port is located, are normally given. For ports in other areas, other publications are given, including United States Coast Pilot (all volumes) and United Kingdom Hydrographic Office Black Sea and Sea of Azov Pilot.

name: Publication_Link
description: A link to the online publication is provided.

name: Standard_Nautical_Chart
description: The number of the best-scale chart issued by NGA is listed with no prefix.

name: IHO_S_57_Electronic_Navigational_Chart
description: The number/name of the appropriate electronic navigational chart in the S-57 format is given.

name: IHO_S_101_Electronic_Navigational_Chart
description: The number/name of the appropriate electronic navigational chart in the S-101 format is given.

name: Digital_Nautical_Chart
description: NGA Digital Nautical Chart library numbers are given.

name: Tidal_Range__m_
description: The mean range in meters is given for all ports. The mean rise is substituted if range data is not available. The distinction between range and rise can be disregarded without affecting the general utility of this Index.

name: Entrance_Width__m_
description: The maximum width of the entrance is given, where restrictions exist.

name: Channel_Depth__m_
description: The controlling depth of the principal or deepest channel at chart datum is given. The channel selected should lead up to the anchorage if within the harbor, or to the wharf/pier. If the channel depth decreases from the anchorage to the wharf/pier and cargo can be worked at the anchorage, then the depth leading to the anchorage is given.

name: Anchorage_Depth__m_
description: The depth in the anchorage is the least depth in the best or principal anchorage. The depth listed reflects a general depth in the anchorage rather than an isolated shoal spot. A shoal which does not necessarily obstruct the anchorage is not considered for the least depth if the rest of the anchorage is safe and practicable.

name: Cargo_Pier_Depth__m_
description: The greatest depth at chart datum alongside the respective wharf/pier is given. If there is more than one wharf/pier, the one which has the greatest usable depth is shown. For example, if there are three cargo/container piers with depths of 7.0 meters, 10.1 meters, and 13.1 meters, then the deepest depth of 13.1 meters would be entered into the Index.

name: Oil_Terminal_Depth__m_
description: The greatest depth at chart datum will be shown. Note: an oil terminal is a facility designed to conduct the loading and/or offloading of crude oil or refined petroleum products. The terminal can be associated with a port or can be a standalone facility. Generally, the terminal is offshore and is connected to the shore facilities by a pipeline. The offshore part may be an extended pier, SBM, buoy field, platform, or storage tanker. Many ports have piers and/or wharves with facilities for refueling vessels. The oil terminal is distinguished by being specifically for oil transfer operations and nothing else (repairs alongside and cargo operations not permitted).

name: Liquified_Natural_Gas_Terminal_Depth__m_
description: The greatest depth at chart datum will be shown. Note: LNG terminals are normally located away from other port operations and operate under an expanded set of safety regulations.

name: Maximum_Vessel_Length__m_
description: The maximum length that can be accommodated in the port is given.

name: Maximum_Vessel_Beam__m_
description: The maximum beam that can be accommodated in the port is given.

name: Maximum_Vessel_Draft__m_
description: The maximum draft that can be accommodated in the port is given.

name: Offshore_Maximum_Vessel_Length__m_
description: The maximum length that can be accommodated offshore is given.

name: Offshore_Maximum_Vessel_Beam__m_
description: The maximum beam that can be accommodated offshore is given.

name: Offshore_Maximum_Vessel_Draft__m_
description: The maximum draft that can be accommodated offshore is given.

name: Harbor_Size
description: The classification of harbor size -- Large, Medium, Small, or Very Small -- is based on several applicable factors, including area, facilities, and wharf space. It is not based on area alone or on any other single factor.

name: Harbor_Type
description: The term "harbor" is used for the principal water area of the port. Harbors are classified as: Coastal (Natural), Coastal (Breakwater), Coastal (Tide Gates), River (Natural), River (Basin), River (Tide Gates), Canal or Lake, or Open Roadstead.

name: Harbor_Use
description: Harbor use is classified as Fishing, Military, Cargo, Ferry, or Unknown.

name: Shelter_Afforded
description: The shelter afforded from wind, sea, and swell refers to the area where normal port operations are conducted, usually the wharf area. Shelter afforded by the anchorage area may be given for ports where cargo is handled by lighters. Values given are Excellent, Good, Fair, Poor, or None.

name: Entrance_Restriction___Tide
description: Natural factor restricting the entrance of vessels -- Tide. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Entrance_Restriction___Heavy_Swell
description: Natural factor restricting the entrance of vessels -- Heavy Swell. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Entrance_Restriction___Ice
description: Natural factor restricting the entrance of vessels -- Ice. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Entrance_Restriction___Other
description: Natural factor restricting the entrance of vessels -- Other. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Overhead_Limits
description: This entry is shown only to indicate that bridge and overhead power cables exist. It is advisable to refer to the chart for particulars. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Underkeel_Clearance_Management_System
description: Indicates whether an Underkeel Clearance Management System is in place in the port or its approaches. Values are Static, Dynamic, None, or Unknown.

name: Good_Holding_Ground
description: This is indicated only where actual anchorage conditions have been reported. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Turning_Area
description: An indication that a turning basin or other water area for turning vessels is available in the port. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Port_Security
description: Indicates whether International Ship and Port Facility Security (ISPS) safety regulations will apply in the port. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Estimated_Time_of_Arrival_Message
description: Indicates whether an ETA message is required for that port. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Quarantine___Pratique
description: Indicates whether pratique will apply to vessels arriving in the port. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Quarantine___Sanitation
description: Indicates whether sanitation will apply to vessels arriving in the port. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Quarantine___Other
description: Indicates whether other restrictions will apply to vessels arriving in the port. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Traffic_Separation_Scheme
description: Indicates if a Traffic Separation Scheme is established in the approach to the port.

name: Vessel_Traffic_Service
description: Indicates that a Vessel Traffic Service is established in the approach to the port. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: First_Port_of_Entry
description: A port where a vessel may enter and clear foreign goods and personnel through Customs and Immigration. For vessels arriving from overseas, a quarantine clearance is required by the First Port of Entry. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: US_Representative
description: Indicates whether the United States maintains civilian/military representation in that port. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Pilotage___Compulsory
description: The necessity or availability of taking a pilot is given. In some cases, pilots are not actually stationed at the port in question and must be obtained elsewhere. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Pilotage___Available
description: The necessity or availability of taking a pilot is given. In some cases, pilotage may be compulsory, although pilots are not actually stationed at the port in question and must be obtained elsewhere. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Pilotage___Local_Assistance
description: The availability of local assistance, as opposed to official pilotage, is given. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Pilotage___Advisable
description: The necessity or availability of taking a pilot, even though not compulsory, is given. In some cases, pilotage may be compulsory, although pilots are not actually stationed at the port in question and must be obtained elsewhere. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Tugs___Salvage
description: Indicates whether tugs are available for salvage assistance. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Tugs___Assistance
description: Indicates whether tugs are available for docking or anchorage assistance. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Communications___Telephone
description: Indicates whether telephone communications are available in the port and/or nearby area. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Communications___Telefax
description: Indicates whether telefax communications are available in the port and/or nearby area. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Communications___Radio
description: Indicates whether radio communications are available in the port and/or nearby area. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Communications___Radiotelephone
description: Indicates whether radiotelephone communications are available in the port and/or nearby area. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Communications___Airport
description: Indicates whether airport communications are available in the port and/or nearby area. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Communications___Rail
description: Indicates whether rail communications are available in the port and/or nearby area. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Search_and_Rescue
description: Indicates whether there are Search and Rescue facilities in the port or nearby area. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: NAVAREA
description: The corresponding NAVAREA, as defined in relevant IMO and IHO documentation, is given.

name: Facilities___Wharves
description: Indicates whether wharf facilities are available in the port and/or nearby area. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Facilities___Anchorage
description: Indicates whether anchorage facilities are available in the port and/or nearby area. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Facilities___Dangerous_Cargo_Anchorage
description: Indicates whether dangerous cargo anchorage facilities are available in the port and/or nearby area. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Facilities___Med_Mooring
description: Indicates whether med mooring facilities are available in the port and/or nearby area. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Facilities___Beach_Mooring
description: Indicates whether beach mooring facilities are available in the port and/or nearby area. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Facilities___Ice_Mooring
description: Indicates whether ice mooring facilities are available in the port and/or nearby area. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Facilities___Ro_Ro
description: Indicates whether ro-ro facilities are available in the port and/or nearby area. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Facilities___Solid_Bulk
description: Indicates whether solid bulk facilities are available in the port and/or nearby area. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Facilities___Liquid_Bulk
description: Indicates whether liquid bulk facilities are available in the port and/or nearby area. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Facilities___Container
description: Indicates whether container facilities are available in the port and/or nearby area. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Facilities___Breakbulk
description: Indicates whether breakbulk facilities are available in the port and/or nearby area. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Facilities___Oil_Terminal
description: Indicates whether oil terminal facilities are available in the port and/or nearby area. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Facilities___LNG_Terminal
description: Indicates whether LNG terminal facilities are available in the port and/or nearby area. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Facilities___Other
description: Indicates whether other facilities are available in the port and/or nearby area. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Medical_Facilities
description: Indicates that there are some form of medical facilities in the port that will accommodate seamen. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Garbage_Disposal
description: Indicates whether garbage can be disposed of at the pier or by lighters at the anchorage or mooring. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Chemical_Holding_Tank_Disposal
description: Indicates whether Chemical Holding Tanks (black water) can be discharged at the pier or at the anchorage. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Degaussing
description: Indicates whether degaussing facilities are available. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Dirty_Ballast_Disposal
description: Pertains to a port that has sufficient facilities for receiving oily and/or chemically contaminated dirty ballast. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Cranes___Fixed
description: Indicates whether fixed cranes are available. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Cranes___Mobile
description: Indicates whether mobile cranes are available. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Cranes___Floating
description: Indicates whether floating cranes are available. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Cranes___Container
description: Indicates whether container cranes are available. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Lifts___100__Tons
description: Indicates the lifting power in tons of the available cranes. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Lifts___50_100_Tons
description: Indicates the lifting power in tons of the available cranes. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Lifts___25_49_Tons
description: Indicates the lifting power in tons of the available cranes. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Lifts___0_24_Tons
description: Indicates the lifting power in tons of the available cranes. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Services___Longshoremen
description: Indicates whether longshoremen services are available. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Services___Electricity
description: Indicates whether electricity services are available. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Services___Steam
description: Indicates whether steam services are available. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Services___Navigation_Equipment
description: Indicates whether navigation equipment services are available. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Services___Electrical_Repair
description: Indicates whether electrical repair services are available. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Services___Ice_Breaking
description: Indicates whether ice breaking services are available. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Services___Diving
description: Indicates whether diving services are available. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Supplies___Provisions
description: The availability of provisions is listed. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Supplies___Potable_Water
description: The availability of water is listed. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Supplies___Fuel_Oil
description: The availability of fuel oil is listed. Fuel and oil types are listed separately, but in cases of original source information failing to distinguish between the two, both kinds are presumed to be available and are so listed. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Supplies___Diesel_Oil
description: The availability of diesel oil is listed. Fuel and oil types are listed separately, but in cases of original source information failing to distinguish between the two, both kinds are presumed to be available and are so listed. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Supplies___Aviation_Fuel
description: The availability of aviation fuel is listed. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Supplies___Deck
description: The availability of deck supplies is listed. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Supplies___Engine
description: The availability of engine supplies is listed. Values are Yes, No, or Unknown.

name: Repairs
description: Repairs that can be made to ocean-going vessels are classified as Major (extensive overhauling and rebuilding in well equipped shipyards), Moderate (extensive overhauling and rebuilding that does not require drydocking, or where suitable facilities are lacking or inadequate), Limited (small repair work in independent machine shops or foundries), Emergency Only, None, or Unknown.

name: Dry_Dock
description: The general size and type of the largest underwater repair facilities in the port are Small (up to 200 meters), Medium (201 - 300 meters), or Large (301 meters and over).

name: Railway
description: The general size and type of the largest underwater repair facilities in the port are Small (up to 200 tons), Medium (201 - 1000 tons), or Large (over 1000 tons).

name: Latitude
description: Latitude of the port is given.

name: Longitude
description: Longitude of the port is given.
